 up all edges together into the middle and pinch edges together to stick. Repeat with remaining dough and pork mixture (makes 12 buns). Place 6 squares of baking paper into Varoma dish and place a bun onto each square with join facing down.","Place remaining 500 g water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma with buns into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until buns are fluffy and firm. Carefully transfer buns into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Top up water if required (to approx. 500 g). Place remaining buns on baking paper squares into Varoma dish, place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <strong><b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b><\/strong>, or until buns are fluffy and firm. Serve buns warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Char siu marinade","content":["30 g piece fresh ginger, peeled","5 garlic cloves","60 g eschalots","2 tsp Chinese five spice","60 g hoi sin sauce","½ tsp ground white pepper","40 g water","30 g molasses","50 g Shaoxing wine","40 g dark soy sauce","1 tbsp tomato sauce","500 g pork belly, cut into 3-4 pieces"]},{"title":"Buns","content":["1 tbsp dried yeast","300 g plain flour","2 tsp baking powder","50 g cornflour","50 g caster sugar","180 g warm water","10 g vegetable oil"]},{"title":"Char siu bao","content":["2 tbsp cornflour","600 g water, plus extra as needed","3 spring onions\/shallots, white and light green part only, cut into pieces (1 cm)","1 tbsp oyster sauce","1 tbsp dark soy sauce"]}],"id":"r118477","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-gI7Fxp4Vhvs\/XZMvGfkvUzI\/AAAAAAAAaNk\/vPUez8tFzmoza1_s2fyPoFin7tf-K8fqgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_YoXT8hBf4NZQz6wq.png","title":"Char siu bao pork buns","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"14.2 g","fat":"8.8 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"33.9 g","calories":"1162 kJ \/ 276 kcal"},"usefulItems":"snaplock bag, sealable container, wire rack, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), pastry brush, bowl, kitche